 based\non the $\\tau_{10}$ /$E(B-V)$ ratio and possible grain crystallinity] that the\ndust in these distant galaxies differs in structure and composition from the\ndust in the Milky Way and the Magellanic Clouds. We briefly discuss the\nimplications of these results for the evolution of galaxies and their star\nformation history.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 21 Mar 2016 14:23:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-12-07"}
